The closer I can find is **[Shaker](http://web.archive.org/web/20140822082955/http:/www.type.co.uk/a_to_z_listing/let/S/id/44159)** by Jeremy Tankard, probably expanded(?), with an /o in place of /zero/

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20140822082955im_/http:/typophile.com/files/shaker-numbers_6270.jpg)

Tankard was right, Shaker was wrong. It is (squooshed) [Corbel](http://web.archive.org/web/20140822082955/http:/www.fontshop.com/fonts/downloads/ascender/corbel_family/pc_tt?&fg=000000&bg=ffffff&sample_size=75&sample_text=303-938-1275&ft=liga).
